Oyo State Government said it has suspended a Secondary school student, Roqeeb Ojo over an alleged assault on a National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) member. Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Barrister Rahman Abiodun Abdu- Raheem made this disclosure on Tuesday. He said the student is a SSS 2 student of Anglican Commercial Secondary School, Orita-Mefa Ibadan. The Commissioner said that the â€œstudent slapped the corp member resulting in the immediate issuance of one-month suspension to the student. The Commissioner, who visited the school also ordered that a letter of suspension be given to the parents of the student. He directed that on his return from suspension, the student, must apologize to the corp member and sign an undertaking. The Commissioner while addressing the students charged them to be of good behaviour, maintaining that the state government will not condone any act of indiscipline. He sternly warned that any student caught, acting in an uncivilized manner, will be dismissed from schools in Oyo State.